  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the <strong>air fryer</strong> to 180°C and boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong>, reserving 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span> <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675267899366-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675267899366-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675267899366-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675267899366-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675267899366-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the pasta is cooking, trim, then slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>lighter cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675267904839-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675267904839-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675267904839-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675267904839-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675267904839-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>sliced spring onion </strong>with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>grated cheddar</strong> in a small bowl</p><p>Add <strong>half </strong>your <strong>pine nuts </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>cheesy stuffing</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675267909715-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675267909715-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675267909715-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675267909715-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1675267909715-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cheesy stuffing </strong>to your <strong>flat white mushrooms </strong>and top with the <strong>remaining pine nuts</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>stuffed mushrooms</strong> to the <strong>air fryer</strong> <strong>basket</strong> with a spray of <strong>olive oil </strong>and cook for 8-10 min or until the cheese is golden and the mushrooms are tender – these are your <strong>cheesy stuffed mushrooms</strong></p><p>Tip: Air fryers work best when the food is spaced out in a single layer. You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
